  "body": "Currently the committee list cache does not handle reorg which invalidates cached shuffled indices at epoch N+1. The program is outlined below:\r\n* At the start of epoch N, a node should be able to cache shuffling for N and N + 1\r\n* Such shuffling is determined by epoch N and randao seed at the start of N\r\n* If the chain reorg such that randao at the start of N is different, then the shuffled indices for N + 1 would be invalidated\r\n* The cache for N + 1 is wrt to epoch N and randao at the start of N\r\n\r\nSolution:\r\nWe should keep old value around if such a reorg because that shows some serious network instability and a node might have multiple branches that you need to be able to validate different shufflings against. Update the cache to be keyed by epoch and epoch boundary block info",
